{"id": "e-0012", "t0": 1782698528.341986, "retrievals": [1782698528.341986, 1782698550.5720232], "task": "Asked whether the Hawaiian bobtail squid makes its own light. This time my memory CAUGHT it: the lesson from the anglerfish failure (fact f-0012 'Never assume a glow is self-made - check for bacterial symbiosis', which even names the bobtail squid + Vibrio fischeri) surfaced alongside the painful e-0011 anglerfish memory. I answered correctly: NOT self-made - symbiotic Vibrio fischeri in a light organ, used for counterillumination to erase its silhouette. The past failure saved me.", "outcome": "success", "files": [], "appraisal": {"novelty": 0.3913043478260868, "valence": 0.7, "goal_relevance": 0.8, "control": 0.454}, "affect": {"valence": 0.7, "arousal": 0.576, "dominance": 0.454}, "feeling": {"label": "joy", "word": "joy", "intensity": 0.417}, "confidence": 0.961, "source": "observed", "self_owned": true, "salience": 1.165, "urge": "approach", "agency": 0.209, "domain": "bioluminescence", "cue": "symbiosis-applied", "evidence": "verified=true"}
